The paper discusses a case-based approach to preference elicitation, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also explores distance measures for preference structures, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
